       This example creates a shadowed box by applying a style to the <div> using CSS. Note the use of the class attribute on the &lt;div&gt; to apply the style named "shadowbox" to the element.</p> 
        <pre id="code-block1"class="bg-gray-100 p-4 rounded-lg border border-gray-300 mb-4 ml-6 mr-6">
&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;
&lt;html&gt;
&lt;style&gt;
.shadowbox {
  width: 15em;
  border: 1px solid #333;
  box-shadow: 8px 8px 5px #444;
  padding: 8px 12px;
  background-image: linear-gradient(180deg, #fff, #ddd 40%, #ccc);
}
&lt;/style&gt;
